title: Ask HN: Notion Alternative
text:
Notion, and most of its competitors, use huge margins. im on a laptop screen and i dont care for wide margins, its taking up too much of my screen space. i want a clean document, write from the left of my screen, to the right. simples.

is there any alternative saas out there that actually lets you uses the width of your screen, or do I have to go back to using ms word and set my own margins?

it seem ridiculous to me that everything has to be so large in web interfaces. buttons, menus, margins, padding...

please help.
